WEBVTT

1
00:00:39.101 --> 00:00:41.701
That's a lot of people.
in this world.

2
00:00:41.861 --> 00:00:45.821
Those who are healthy and not sick.
Those who are men. and not women.

3
00:00:45.981 --> 00:00:50.181
Those who are wise. not stupid.
Beautiful and not ugly.

4
00:00:50.341 --> 00:00:54.181
And then there are them
which is everything at once.

5
00:00:55.661 --> 00:01:00.141
Baldur and Arni
were both healthy. beautiful and wise.

6
00:01:00.301 --> 00:01:03.101
They were sons of the great chief.

7
00:01:04.061 --> 00:01:08.341
Once home from a cruise. he gave
them an axe with a handle of mother-of-pearl -

8
00:01:08.501 --> 00:01:11.341
- from the seas
on the back of the world.

9
00:01:18.861 --> 00:01:24.141
But one summer day the village came under
attack and everyone had to take cover.

10
00:01:25.301 --> 00:01:30.501
For little Baldur the axe was
too heavy. and it cost him time.

11
00:01:42.461 --> 00:01:45.541
Baldur lost
his left arm that day -

12
00:01:45.701 --> 00:01:49.861
- and his reality
was changed forever and ever.

13
00:01:50.021 --> 00:01:54.541
The feeling of being different
and the outcast consumed his mind -

14
00:01:54.701 --> 00:01:59.581
- and suddenly didn't know
Baldur no longer knew who he was.

15
00:01:59.741 --> 00:02:04.581
He didn't feel well.
wise or beautiful anymore.

16
00:02:04.741 --> 00:02:08.541
He had become less valuable.
than the others.

17
00:02:09.421 --> 00:02:14.261
The great chief. who had sworn
that everyone was of equal worth -

18
00:02:14.421 --> 00:02:19.101
- couldn't just watch while
his youngest son perished.

19
00:02:19.261 --> 00:02:23.981
He decided that everyone
boys. men. old and newborn -

20
00:02:24.141 --> 00:02:29.061
- during his greatness
also had to give his left arm.

21
00:02:30.421 --> 00:02:36.061
He knew that if everyone is gone in
pieces. none have broken.

22
00:02:39.701 --> 00:02:44.021
And when Baldur's reality
could not be changed -

23
00:02:44.181 --> 00:02:48.541
- then the reality around him had to
change instead.

24
00:02:48.701 --> 00:02:54.101
THE LAST VIKING

25
00:03:27.261 --> 00:03:29.861
...robbers forced their way in -

26
00:03:30.021 --> 00:03:33.501
- to the value management center
Loomis in Glostrup.

27
00:03:33.661 --> 00:03:37.341
The robbers are described as brutal.
and very targeted.

28
00:03:37.501 --> 00:03:42.341
Several witnesses have seen two cars
in the area at the time of the crime.

29
00:03:42.501 --> 00:03:44.821
What's going on. Anchor?

30
00:03:44.981 --> 00:03:48.381
Pack a travel bag for me. Freja.
And find the passport. Now!

31
00:03:48.541 --> 00:03:53.101
Hold up now.
Stop it! Help me!

32
00:03:54.181 --> 00:03:57.461
- Manfred...
- We're having a barbecue tonight.

33
00:03:57.621 --> 00:04:02.741
- We're going to have big chops.
- I'll have to go away.

34
00:04:02.901 --> 00:04:06.341
- You have to do something for me.
- Where are you going?

35
00:04:06.501 --> 00:04:11.181
- Everything will be fine. Freja is here.
- I want you to be here too.

36
00:04:11.341 --> 00:04:17.021
I'll be back. okay?
You must eat this key...

37
00:04:18.341 --> 00:04:21.501
Sometimes you have to let me
Finish talking first.

38
00:04:21.661 --> 00:04:27.261
When it comes out. swallow.
it again. until everything is safe.

39
00:04:27.421 --> 00:04:29.861
Do you hear what I'm saying?

40
00:04:31.341 --> 00:04:35.541
At the train station. locker number 23.
You have the key now.

41
00:04:35.701 --> 00:04:40.821
In that closet there is a bag. Grave
it down in the forest up by mother's house -

42
00:04:40.981 --> 00:04:45.301
- at the old oak table
where we celebrated your birthday.

43
00:04:45.461 --> 00:04:49.741
Can you do that for me?
You're the only one I can trust.

44
00:04:49.901 --> 00:04:54.581
- Can I bury it somewhere else?
- Anchor. you have to come.

45
00:04:54.741 --> 00:04:56.501
Anchor.

46
00:05:02.301 --> 00:05:04.341
MONEY TRANSPORT ROBBERY

47
00:05:48.421 --> 00:05:50.861
Who are you. Anchor?

48
00:05:51.021 --> 00:05:54.581
I am Anchor.
I am Anker Andersen.

49
00:05:54.741 --> 00:05:58.541
Are you the model prisoner. who
deserves to be released on parole -

50
00:05:58.701 --> 00:06:01.901
- or Anchor
who beat a fellow inmate 31 times -

51
00:06:02.061 --> 00:06:05.141
- because he spilled coffee
about your sudoku?

52
00:06:05.301 --> 00:06:09.861
Or Anchor robbing a bank-
transportation and aiding and abetting murder?

53
00:06:10.021 --> 00:06:13.341
I am many things.
but I am not a murderer.

54
00:06:13.501 --> 00:06:16.381
I have never killed anyone.

55
00:06:17.701 --> 00:06:23.021
I have had a lot of anger in me.
against many people.

56
00:06:23.181 --> 00:06:26.341
To my family. To my father...

57
00:06:27.301 --> 00:06:30.741
...because he left us.
Against my brother.

58
00:06:32.181 --> 00:06:37.221
But I have been ordered to
my temperament and myself.

59
00:06:37.381 --> 00:06:43.421
What do you have to say about 41.2 million
never been found?

60
00:06:43.621 --> 00:06:48.101
I have... I have reviewed
this process with you many times.

61
00:06:48.261 --> 00:06:53.741
If I knew where the money was.
I would have told you that a long time ago.

62
00:06:55.781 --> 00:07:00.381
Listen. I'm drug-free.
and I haven't had a drink in 11 years.

63
00:07:00.541 --> 00:07:05.981
I'm not violent anymore. I know.
Not sure what else I can do.

64
00:07:06.901 --> 00:07:11.901
I can only say that I am different.
than I was at that time.

65
00:07:13.421 --> 00:07:16.741
WELCOME HOME FROM PRISON ANCHOR

66
00:07:25.261 --> 00:07:28.821
- Won't you open the door?
- No. I'll wait a little longer.

67
00:07:29.701 --> 00:07:31.821
Can you...

68
00:07:36.301 --> 00:07:39.181
- Hello. my brother.
- Hey.

69
00:07:40.901 --> 00:07:43.941
He has bought 60
of your favorite rolls.

70
00:07:44.101 --> 00:07:46.861
He hasn't slept in a week.

71
00:07:56.421 --> 00:08:01.421
Do you think that's enough rolls?
Or what. Manfred?

72
00:08:01.621 --> 00:08:06.701
- I forgot. His name is John now.
- Why is that?

73
00:08:06.861 --> 00:08:11.261
Because he doesn't want to be called Manfred.
Everyone calls him John.

74
00:08:11.421 --> 00:08:17.381
Those flowers were picked by John.
and dried and glued them up like that.

75
00:08:17.541 --> 00:08:23.101
That's great. Why the fuck
Don't you want to be called Manfred anymore?

76
00:08:23.261 --> 00:08:25.981
- What is it?
- Here. John...

77
00:08:26.141 --> 00:08:28.741
Stop it there.

78
00:08:34.301 --> 00:08:38.261
You can't just come home.
and believe that everything is the same.

79
00:08:38.421 --> 00:08:41.101
Everything has gotten worse since mom died.

80
00:08:41.261 --> 00:08:45.061
He has missed you so much.
and now he thinks you're leaving again.

81
00:08:45.221 --> 00:08:49.101
Can't you say sorry?
and say you're going to stay now?

82
00:08:49.261 --> 00:08:53.941
I'm thinking of taking a trip.
Up to mom's house or something.

83
00:08:54.101 --> 00:08:58.181
That's a good idea. Then you can
stay up there for a few days.

84
00:08:58.341 --> 00:09:02.581
Those who have bought the house
Renting to Airbnb.

85
00:09:02.781 --> 00:09:06.461
But just remember to call him John. okay?
John?

86
00:09:21.981 --> 00:09:25.981
Whoops. you have to apologize for that.
It became very dramatic.

87
00:09:26.141 --> 00:09:30.701
What the hell are you doing? We don't have any more
to do with each other. Flemming.

88
00:09:30.861 --> 00:09:34.981
I must have all your money.
Anchor. otherwise things will go wrong.

89
00:09:35.141 --> 00:09:38.021
All my money?
You've got your half.

90
00:09:38.181 --> 00:09:42.781
I have used them up. and I have
got me into a lot of debt -

91
00:09:42.941 --> 00:09:45.981
- and I have promised people
that you would help me.

92
00:09:46.141 --> 00:09:48.821
No. now I want to hit you.

93
00:09:48.981 --> 00:09:53.741
- How much do you owe?
- I must have all 20 million.

94
00:09:57.301 --> 00:10:02.181
But you have until Monday.
What's with that door frame?

95
00:10:02.341 --> 00:10:05.821
It's fucking dangerous.
You know what?

96
00:10:05.981 --> 00:10:11.061
I'll fix it. I'll bring it.
some tools on Monday.

97
00:10:13.661 --> 00:10:16.101
Do you want to eat another one?

98
00:10:16.261 --> 00:10:20.261
You are welcome to do so.
Would you like to eat another one?

99
00:10:20.421 --> 00:10:24.581
- Where did you get the dog from?
- That's our dog now. Anker.

100
00:10:24.741 --> 00:10:27.781
If you stay here.
Would you like that?

101
00:10:27.941 --> 00:10:32.301
Do you want to go swimming together?
with me and the dog. Anker?

102
00:10:33.381 --> 00:10:36.381
Yes. now we have a new dog.

103
00:10:39.381 --> 00:10:42.581
Give me the dog.
Bente is standing down.

104
00:10:42.781 --> 00:10:46.741
- Give it to me. Bente is standing downstairs.
- Which dog?

105
00:10:46.901 --> 00:10:51.901
- That dog. damn it!
- Then it's hidden there again.

106
00:10:52.061 --> 00:10:54.861
So it would like to live here. then.

107
00:10:55.021 --> 00:10:57.981
I'll give it some water.

108
00:10:58.141 --> 00:11:01.501
No! That's not her dog.
There is another dog.

109
00:11:01.661 --> 00:11:04.981
And then right now. when it loves me
and Anker saw a lot.

110
00:11:05.141 --> 00:11:09.461
- Come here. Bente is calling the police.
- We shouldn't have any police here.

111
00:11:09.661 --> 00:11:13.421
- Give her the dog now. Manfred!
- Call him John. for God's sake!

112
00:11:18.581 --> 00:11:22.781
- Then it could be the same!
- He takes people's dogs.

113
00:11:22.941 --> 00:11:26.661
Everyone in the hallway is sick of him.
You have to call him John.

114
00:11:26.821 --> 00:11:30.581
Last week I forgot about it. and then
he stabbed himself with a meat fork.

115
00:11:30.781 --> 00:11:33.621
John... John.

116
00:11:36.021 --> 00:11:39.341
If I stand
at the old oak table -

117
00:11:39.501 --> 00:11:44.101
- where in relation to the table
Have you buried the bag?

118
00:11:44.261 --> 00:11:47.381
Stop it. Manfred.

119
00:11:48.381 --> 00:11:52.741
- I don't know who you're talking to.
- Stop it now. I don't want that.

120
00:11:52.901 --> 00:11:56.021
- Why do you want to be called John?
- Because I'm John.

121
00:11:56.181 --> 00:12:00.421
- But why are you John?
- But why are you Anker?

122
00:12:00.581 --> 00:12:04.741
I don't give a damn what you think.
I am John.

123
00:12:04.901 --> 00:12:06.901
John Lennon.

124
00:12:08.581 --> 00:12:10.581
John Lennon?

125
00:12:10.741 --> 00:12:15.621
Now you can fucking clap me again!
Excuse me. but what the hell is going on?

126
00:12:15.781 --> 00:12:21.181
You don't even look like him.
You don't even have the right glasses.

127
00:12:22.661 --> 00:12:27.581
I drive them and save up for them.
You have to accept this. or else...

128
00:12:27.741 --> 00:12:31.741
Otherwise you'll stab yourself.
in the head with a fondue skewer?

129
00:12:31.901 --> 00:12:36.141
I can slowly kill myself.
with a spear like that. yes.

130
00:12:36.301 --> 00:12:41.501
I had big plans for it.
But we never get fondue.

131
00:12:41.661 --> 00:12:45.541
Hold up now.
Manfred. now you tell me where it is...

132
00:13:10.901 --> 00:13:13.221
- Is he okay?
- Who?

133
00:13:13.381 --> 00:13:16.021
My brother. Manfred Andersen.

134
00:13:16.181 --> 00:13:19.341
Well. Andersen? It's just...
superficial scratches.

135
00:13:19.501 --> 00:13:22.421
Then I can take him home. right?

136
00:13:22.581 --> 00:13:27.541
We have to keep him. since...
is it a suicide attempt -

137
00:13:27.701 --> 00:13:33.061
- but you drop a 500-rupee note
in my pocket. then you can take him.

138
00:13:33.221 --> 00:13:37.501
- Do you want me to bribe you?
- Jaggu. someone got angry.

139
00:13:37.661 --> 00:13:42.261
- But what the hell are you thinking about?
- It was a joke. damn it.

140
00:13:43.501 --> 00:13:46.341
Your brother is down at 8C.

141
00:14:02.021 --> 00:14:04.021
Are you okay?

142
00:14:04.901 --> 00:14:07.941
Can you sit in a car?

143
00:14:09.421 --> 00:14:13.781
I understand that.
You've missed me.

144
00:14:13.941 --> 00:14:18.341
And you are confused and hurt by
that I haven't been there.

145
00:14:18.501 --> 00:14:21.541
Yes... But now I'm here.

146
00:14:23.621 --> 00:14:25.901
Come on.

147
00:14:27.901 --> 00:14:33.101
I want you to ride up with me.
and shows where that bag is.

148
00:14:33.261 --> 00:14:37.221
Then we'll do something together afterwards.
Isn't that right. Manfred?

149
00:14:57.221 --> 00:14:59.861
Are you okay?

150
00:15:00.021 --> 00:15:02.901
Can I hold it?

151
00:15:06.901 --> 00:15:09.941
Yes. now we're away from that stupid woman.

152
00:15:13.861 --> 00:15:16.581
Dissociative
personality disorder.

153
00:15:16.781 --> 00:15:19.341
When the rest of us are one person -

154
00:15:19.501 --> 00:15:23.341
- then Manfred switches between
several different personalities -

155
00:15:23.541 --> 00:15:27.141
- and now he's locked up in
an alter ego like John Lennon.

156
00:15:27.301 --> 00:15:32.461
I have to take him with me.
I need to talk to him.

157
00:15:32.621 --> 00:15:36.181
You have missed him.
but Manfred is going to stay here.

158
00:15:36.341 --> 00:15:39.181
Why that?
He hasn't done anything to anyone.

159
00:15:39.341 --> 00:15:45.181
He has attempted suicide and stolen.
nine dogs since October last year.

160
00:15:45.341 --> 00:15:49.781
Manfred knows who he is.
This is something he plays.

161
00:15:49.941 --> 00:15:53.381
It is usually
a year-long process -

162
00:15:53.541 --> 00:15:57.541
- involving a combination
of therapy and medicine.

163
00:15:57.701 --> 00:16:02.501
And some patients remain
his alter ego for the rest of his life.

164
00:16:02.661 --> 00:16:06.421
We know that dissociative
personality disorder -

165
00:16:06.581 --> 00:16:10.741
- occurs due to traumatic events
experiences earlier in life.

166
00:16:10.901 --> 00:16:14.221
It could be 10. 20. 30 years ago.

167
00:16:38.341 --> 00:16:39.541
Manfred!

168
00:16:50.061 --> 00:16:52.901
What the hell are you doing?
He's killing us.

169
00:16:55.661 --> 00:16:59.821
That axe will be hanging here.
And take off your helmet. We have to go to school.

170
00:16:59.981 --> 00:17:03.221
- No. I'm going on a cruise.
- No. you shouldn't.

171
00:17:03.381 --> 00:17:08.381
Stop behaving so abnormally.
You're too big. Everyone's laughing at you.

172
00:17:17.661 --> 00:17:21.181
You are not a Viking.
Vikings don't exist.

173
00:17:22.701 --> 00:17:25.021
I exist.

174
00:17:25.181 --> 00:17:27.821
Anchor. are you in there?

175
00:17:31.181 --> 00:17:34.821
YACHT FOR SALE

176
00:17:37.101 --> 00:17:40.421
There we have the chairman of
the anti-corruption department.

177
00:17:40.581 --> 00:17:43.221
Eight Fernet Branca. Lilian. Thank you.

178
00:17:43.381 --> 00:17:47.421
Lothar Nielsen from psychiatry.
Do you remember me?

179
00:17:47.621 --> 00:17:52.181
- Are you going sailing with your brother?
- No. he came to a closed ward.

180
00:17:52.341 --> 00:17:55.021
That might be very good.

181
00:17:55.181 --> 00:17:59.901
- Has he received a diagnosis?
- Dissociative personality disorder...

182
00:18:00.061 --> 00:18:03.381
Dissociative
personality disorder.

183
00:18:05.741 --> 00:18:07.901
Did you ask for eight Fernet Branca?
to yourself?

184
00:18:08.061 --> 00:18:12.781
I always order eight.
Otherwise it looks so violent.

185
00:18:12.941 --> 00:18:18.221
Dissociative personality disorder
is a real crappy diagnosis.

186
00:18:18.381 --> 00:18:22.181
It's madness.
He thinks he's John Lennon.

187
00:18:25.101 --> 00:18:27.941
I had a Michael Laudrup
in custody.

188
00:18:28.101 --> 00:18:30.821
He also alternated between
Jesus and John Wayne.

189
00:18:30.981 --> 00:18:35.381
It was completely impossible for the kitchen
to know what they were going to serve.

190
00:18:35.541 --> 00:18:40.021
There's a guy sitting outside on Amager
who thinks he's Ringo Starr.

191
00:18:40.181 --> 00:18:44.981
Then we just need Paul and George.
then we can get the band together.

192
00:18:49.221 --> 00:18:54.221
Why is things going so wrong for him now?
He should be happy to see me.

193
00:18:54.381 --> 00:18:57.981
He has been able to handle
the subpersonality until now -

194
00:18:58.141 --> 00:19:02.661
- because there has been no conflict
between self-image and the environment.

195
00:19:02.821 --> 00:19:05.301
I don't understand a damn thing about that.

196
00:19:05.461 --> 00:19:08.861
Let's say I walk around
and will be called Napoleon.

197
00:19:09.021 --> 00:19:12.021
Then my surroundings will
consider me an idiot.

198
00:19:12.181 --> 00:19:15.101
It will affect
my self-image is negative.

199
00:19:15.261 --> 00:19:19.621
But if we build a copy of
Versailles. hires 200 servants -

200
00:19:19.781 --> 00:19:22.341
- give me an army
and teach me French -

201
00:19:22.501 --> 00:19:25.381
- then it's not so strange
that I am Napoleon -

202
00:19:25.541 --> 00:19:28.941
- and therefore my self-image will
remain intact.

203
00:19:29.101 --> 00:19:32.661
As long as the surroundings play along.
then everything is fine.

204
00:19:32.821 --> 00:19:36.901
The whole neighborhood calls him John.
He fucking writes autographs.

205
00:19:37.061 --> 00:19:40.381
I can't just pretend then
He is John Lennon.

206
00:19:40.541 --> 00:19:44.501
- Wouldn't that be completely wrong?
- Where have you been for the last 20 years?

207
00:19:44.661 --> 00:19:48.141
When IKEA opened. it was
46 different item numbers.

208
00:19:48.301 --> 00:19:52.101
Today there are 12.000 products.
Everyone has become unique.

209
00:19:52.261 --> 00:19:55.421
Everyone has the right to
its own unique reality.

210
00:19:55.621 --> 00:19:59.621
Then you can probably fix it too.
calling your brother John Lennon.

211
00:20:43.181 --> 00:20:46.421
Good thing you're up.
You have to look here.

212
00:20:46.581 --> 00:20:50.781
- Please. a shirt for you.
- How long have I been sleeping here?

213
00:20:50.941 --> 00:20:55.701
I drove past the patient registry for
to see if Ringo is still sitting there.

214
00:20:57.701 --> 00:21:01.541
Ok. One Anton Wulf Espersen -

215
00:21:01.701 --> 00:21:05.501
- was admitted in July 1996
at the psychiatric center on Amager -

216
00:21:05.661 --> 00:21:10.581
- and thinks he's the drummer
Ringo Starr fra The Beatles.

217
00:21:10.781 --> 00:21:13.821
It was your own idea.
I checked all departments.

218
00:21:13.981 --> 00:21:15.861
What was my own idea?

219
00:21:16.021 --> 00:21:20.261
Gathering The Beatles to surround
Manfred with his own reality.

220
00:21:20.421 --> 00:21:24.661
But Paul McCartney and George Harrison
was tricky. There is no one in Denmark.

221
00:21:24.821 --> 00:21:27.661
I was really about to give up -

222
00:21:27.821 --> 00:21:31.221
- but look here.
Who is sitting in Sweden?

223
00:21:31.381 --> 00:21:34.581
