my first beaver when I was three.

445
00:43:08.461 --> 00:43:12.981
- Get in the crazy bus and drive again.
- Try to see the potential here. then!

446
00:43:13.141 --> 00:43:16.301
It is a valid
psychiatric experiment...

447
00:43:16.461 --> 00:43:20.301
- We're not forming a band with idiots!
- That's not for you to decide.

448
00:43:20.461 --> 00:43:24.381
- Now listen here...
- Take it easy. Relax!

449
00:43:24.541 --> 00:43:27.141
Anchor. I'm going to die!

450
00:43:27.301 --> 00:43:30.741
Excuse me.
I shouldn't have said that.

451
00:43:30.901 --> 00:43:33.621
But I have
advanced prostate cancer.

452
00:43:33.781 --> 00:43:38.781
And this is a last chance for
to achieve something within that subject -

453
00:43:38.941 --> 00:43:42.981
- after all. I have dedicated...
my whole life.

454
00:43:44.381 --> 00:43:48.421
I'm sorry to hear that.
but you can't be here.

455
00:43:48.581 --> 00:43:54.421
You are making a mistake. It is your best
chance to get Manfred back.

456
00:43:54.581 --> 00:43:59.021
But I'm throwing in the towel.
I can't take it anymore.

457
00:44:02.581 --> 00:44:04.701
Lothar.

458
00:44:04.861 --> 00:44:08.381
How long would it take?
before he became himself?

459
00:44:08.541 --> 00:44:14.101
Then you would see progress soon.
Once they have practiced a couple of numbers.

460
00:44:14.261 --> 00:44:18.221
- Are you sure about that?
- Yes. You won't regret it.

461
00:44:20.101 --> 00:44:22.861
- It's something else.
- And?

462
00:44:24.381 --> 00:44:27.261
Manfred remembered
where our dog was buried.

463
00:44:27.421 --> 00:44:32.301
He may be in contact with
the subconscious of one's true self.

464
00:44:32.461 --> 00:44:35.621
But... I didn't know.
that we had a dog.

465
00:44:35.781 --> 00:44:41.381
Or. I completely forgot about it.
Isn't it strange to forget?

466
00:44:41.541 --> 00:44:46.261
The brain forgets indifferent things.
It's completely normal.

467
00:44:46.421 --> 00:44:49.621
What if it isn't?
Indifferent things? But important?

468
00:44:49.781 --> 00:44:53.941
Yes. that's even more normal.
But it's a long conversation.

469
00:44:54.101 --> 00:44:57.261
Focus on the band
and to get Manfred back.

470
00:44:57.421 --> 00:45:01.821
You have to see Paul George play.
He is absolutely amazing.

471
00:45:07.821 --> 00:45:11.261
- Aren't you coming out?
- No. I don't.

472
00:45:11.421 --> 00:45:16.421
- That's really rude.
- That's crazy! Listen!

473
00:45:33.341 --> 00:45:38.101
- Aren't they supposed to play the same song?
- It is important not to interfere.

474
00:45:38.261 --> 00:45:40.901
They should probably play the same.

475
00:45:41.061 --> 00:45:44.421
- The ugly one says I'm bad.
- Everyone is equally good.

476
00:45:44.581 --> 00:45:48.301
You must not lie.
I know I'm not that good.

477
00:45:48.461 --> 00:45:51.581
You have to play worse.
so it's not my fault.

478
00:45:51.741 --> 00:45:56.021
I don't see anyone to blame.
I just see a lot of talent.

479
00:45:56.181 --> 00:45:59.381
Yes. yes. exactly.
We are all the best.

480
00:45:59.541 --> 00:46:03.461
Everything was Anker's idea. but he
Not saying he's better than anyone.

481
00:46:03.621 --> 00:46:07.381
If you want to be successful with
An idea must be promoted in a group.

482
00:46:07.541 --> 00:46:11.501
An idea is not just an idea.
You have to have the logistics in order -

483
00:46:11.661 --> 00:46:16.261
- have the crew to carry it out.
and then you have to have a plan.

484
00:46:16.421 --> 00:46:19.661
So a bit like the Holocaust?

485
00:46:19.821 --> 00:46:23.781
- Then I'm out!
- IKEA would be a better example.

486
00:46:23.941 --> 00:46:27.661
But let's take it again.
Try again. Come on.

487
00:46:42.301 --> 00:46:44.701
Stop. stop!

488
00:46:45.661 --> 00:46:50.821
That doesn't sound good.
We have to play together. Okay?

489
00:46:52.341 --> 00:46:56.061
- E major. Follow me.
- What is he doing now?

490
00:46:56.221 --> 00:47:00.021
- Will he become McCartney?
- Yes. now he's changing his identity.

491
00:47:00.181 --> 00:47:05.901
It is wonderful to witness.
Now he goes from George to Paul.

492
00:47:17.941 --> 00:47:21.461
Hamdan also believes
that he is Björn from ABBA.

493
00:47:23.261 --> 00:47:26.141
He also believes that he is
Heinrich Himmler -

494
00:47:26.301 --> 00:47:29.021
- which gave us problems on the ferry.

495
00:47:29.181 --> 00:47:33.501
He'll be George again soon.
Or Paul.

496
00:47:43.501 --> 00:47:47.661
It's just too annoying.
We shouldn't listen to anything like that.

497
00:47:47.821 --> 00:47:50.101
No. don't!

498
00:48:06.261 --> 00:48:10.021
When IKEA opened its first store
in Denmark in 1969 -

499
00:48:10.181 --> 00:48:12.461
- many things were not in place.

500
00:48:12.621 --> 00:48:17.981
That was before barcodes. The idea of
Selling inventory that way was new.

501
00:48:18.141 --> 00:48:23.221
But they had faith in things. The
the same faith we all have here today.

502
00:48:23.381 --> 00:48:26.421
The band is reunited.
One notices that -

503
00:48:26.581 --> 00:48:31.181
- you are among the best. and that
They will also notice down in the city.

504
00:48:31.341 --> 00:48:34.501
Because this morning I paid
the registration fee -

505
00:48:34.661 --> 00:48:39.141
- for 250 kr more
the talent competition down at the inn.

506
00:48:39.301 --> 00:48:43.981
That's not impressive.
but we must crawl before we can walk.

507
00:48:44.141 --> 00:48:49.661
We start small and work our way up.
slowly up. Completely like IKEA.

508
00:48:49.821 --> 00:48:52.701
- Cheers!
- Cheers.

509
00:48:52.861 --> 00:48:57.461
- Should we play for the audience?
- No. just for a lot of beavers.

510
00:48:57.621 --> 00:49:03.301
240 extremely musical beavers
who claps along to all the numbers.

511
00:49:03.461 --> 00:49:05.941
- But isn't that dangerous?
- Because.

512
00:49:06.101 --> 00:49:11.021
If you get stage fright. then
Imagine the audience is beavers.

513
00:49:17.501 --> 00:49:22.941
- Can't you stop with that?
- No. Björn says I should practice.

514
00:49:23.101 --> 00:49:27.941
But I would like to ask Lothar
if you can join in and play bass.

515
00:49:32.581 --> 00:49:35.541
I'm better at the mosquito song.

516
00:49:44.901 --> 00:49:48.501
Incredible. one can be both dumb
and snore like that.

517
00:49:48.661 --> 00:49:51.901
Deaf people also dream with sound.
And color blind.

518
00:49:52.061 --> 00:49:57.381
I dream in German.
It's not because of the Holocaust.

519
00:49:57.541 --> 00:50:01.501
I never dream of that.
because I wasn't there.

520
00:50:01.661 --> 00:50:05.141
I curse.
my Aryan origins.

521
00:50:06.341 --> 00:50:09.981
When I was young.
I dyed my hair black.

522
00:50:13.301 --> 00:50:16.381
And wore dark contact lenses.

523
00:50:21.141 --> 00:50:25.901
You know what? Now I think you should
Sleep. You're tired. Paul George.

524
00:50:26.061 --> 00:50:31.781
There's no Paul George here.
It's just Björn. Accept it.

525
00:50:31.941 --> 00:50:36.181
Now we sleep. and then we find out
who we are tomorrow. right?

526
00:51:23.861 --> 00:51:26.701
That's great. Thank you.

527
00:51:26.861 --> 00:51:32.181
You really have it under control.
So we don't need to play it anymore.

528
00:51:32.341 --> 00:51:36.181
- Aren't they supposed to play the Beatles?
- It's coming. Werner.

529
00:51:36.341 --> 00:51:41.621
But now I think we should try.
to draw the breath down into the belly.

530
00:51:41.781 --> 00:51:45.341
And breathe out through your nose. Like that.

531
00:51:45.501 --> 00:51:50.181
Maybe we should try playing
"With a Little Help from My Friends".

532
00:51:50.341 --> 00:51:52.901
What Werner had suggested.

533
00:51:53.061 --> 00:51:56.421
I don't understand what it is.
is about. It is missing a layer.

534
00:51:56.581 --> 00:51:59.341
- What does he say?
- That it's missing a layer.

535
00:51:59.501 --> 00:52:02.181
You just sang about a banana.

536
00:52:02.341 --> 00:52:05.341
He can't talk to me.
because then I'm out!

537
00:52:05.501 --> 00:52:09.581
Now let's take it easy.
Now let's be kind to each other.

538
00:52:09.741 --> 00:52:12.901
John. can't you
explain to us a little about -

539
00:52:13.061 --> 00:52:16.821
- hva "With a Little Help
from My Friends" handler om.

540
00:52:16.981 --> 00:52:22.101
- Could I answer that?
- What are all people afraid of?

541
00:52:22.261 --> 00:52:24.781
What do we fear the most?

542
00:52:24.941 --> 00:52:27.821
- Vikings.
- Holocaust.

543
00:52:27.981 --> 00:52:33.621
Yes... Yes. maybe. But even more
Afraid of? I can give you a hint.

544
00:52:33.781 --> 00:52:37.261
IKEA employees have something
which is called a "code 99".

545
00:52:37.421 --> 00:52:40.541
It's when a child has gone missing -

546
00:52:40.701 --> 00:52:44.301
- because the worst
that can happen to a child is -

547
00:52:44.461 --> 00:52:46.941
- that they think they are alone.

548
00:52:48.581 --> 00:52:49.581
Hamdan?

549
00:52:49.741 --> 00:52:53.381
I think the song is about children.
who is alone at IKEA.

550
00:52:53.541 --> 00:52:57.181
I also think it's about
some children living at IKEA.

551
00:52:57.341 --> 00:52:59.821
That's exactly it.
it is about.

552
00:52:59.981 --> 00:53:04.301
"With a Little Help from My Friends"
It's about never being alone.

553
00:53:04.461 --> 00:53:10.421
That you always have some people
who you trust. who will be there.

554
00:53:10.581 --> 00:53:13.021
Do you feel that way about anyone?

555
00:53:13.181 --> 00:53:18.461
Someone you trust. but who you
Maybe I'm afraid I'll leave you?

556
00:53:23.021 --> 00:53:27.941
Yes... Shouldn't we try?
to play something else now?

557
00:54:01.781 --> 00:54:06.661
Oops... Sorry. That was really...
dramatic. That wasn't the intention.

558
00:54:06.821 --> 00:54:10.141
- Do you know who I am?
- In the...

559
00:54:10.301 --> 00:54:15.741
People call me Flinke Flemming.
Do you know where Anker is?

560
00:54:16.541 --> 00:54:18.861
Get up.

561
00:54:23.941 --> 00:54:28.701
Let's go up and wait for him.
We'll figure everything out. Come on.

562
00:54:38.661 --> 00:54:41.661
Everyone would like to be someone else.

563
00:54:41.821 --> 00:54:46.501
- The young will be older and vice versa.
- What does it help to play ABBA?

564
00:54:46.661 --> 00:54:51.741
- We've been listening to jazz for 20 years now.
- So now jazz is also completely wrong?

565
00:54:51.901 --> 00:54:56.901
When you hear it that way.
in silence with red wine and analyses.

566
00:54:57.061 --> 00:54:59.981
It says idiot
all over our face.

567
00:55:00.141 --> 00:55:05.981
I've gotten more out of listening to Paul
George sings. but at a very long time.

568
00:55:06.141 --> 00:55:10.421
His name is Björn. He takes his own life.
if you call him that again.

569
00:55:10.581 --> 00:55:13.341
You can't just choose
his own name.

570
00:55:13.501 --> 00:55:17.101
You deserve it.
or received from their parents.

571
00:55:17.261 --> 00:55:20.421
I can't call myself
for kong Werner.

572
00:55:20.581 --> 00:55:24.581
- It must reflect reality.
- Let others come. Werner.

573
00:55:24.741 --> 00:55:27.821
If everything is worth the same.
is nothing worth anything.

574
00:55:27.981 --> 00:55:32.101
Jazz and the Beatles are better than ABBA.
Healthy is better than sick.

575
00:55:32.261 --> 00:55:36.021
There are objective truths
which cannot be discussed.

576
00:55:36.181 --> 00:55:38.821
You have to have a shared reality.

577
00:55:38.981 --> 00:55:42.341
That's absolutely crazy. Margrethe.

578
00:55:42.501 --> 00:55:47.141
Now you can't recognize yourself.
Just because you heard a song?

579
00:55:47.301 --> 00:55:52.741
Margrethe just wants to be accepted
of the outside world as who she is.

580
00:55:52.901 --> 00:55:57.901
When you look like me.
No one sees you for who you are.

581
00:55:58.061 --> 00:56:00.981
Everyone thinks you're stupid.
when you are pretty.

582
00:56:01.141 --> 00:56:05.501
Only when I got together with Werner.
People started taking me seriously.

583
00:56:05.661 --> 00:56:11.181
When they could see that I openly didn't
went for looks or money -

584
00:56:11.341 --> 00:56:15.221
- but sought an intellect
I could see myself in the mirror.

585
00:56:15.381 --> 00:56:17.381
I understand you.

586
00:56:17.541 --> 00:56:24.181
I have been in many relationships where
They didn't take me for my qualities.

587
00:56:24.341 --> 00:56:29.181
They just wanted a trophy girlfriend
with the perfect Nordic look.

588
00:56:31.181 --> 00:56:36.501
My blond hair and my blue eyes
has always been a curse.

589
00:57:42.341 --> 00:57:45.301
What are you digging for?

590
00:57:47.101 --> 00:57:48.901
Mark.

591
00:57:49.061 --> 00:57:53.421
- With a metal detector?
- Yes. that...

592
00:57:53.621 --> 00:57:57.781
I just like to dig.
and see what I find.

593
00:57:57.941 --> 00:58:03.101
Okay. But then we're down to zero.
normal people on the register.

594
00:58:04.461 --> 00:58:10.221
I think it's absolutely amazing to see
How to take care of your brother.

595
00:58:10.381 --> 00:58:16.541
So. all that stuff about the band
and bring him back here and...

596
00:58:18.461 --> 00:58:24.821
- Okay. I think I'll dig further.
- Okay. I won't disturb you.

597
00:58:24.981 --> 00:58:28.341
- I need four kilometers.
- What do you say?

598
00:58:28.501 --> 00:58:33.181
- I need four kilometers.
- Yes. Okay.

599
00:58:47.461 --> 00:58:51.101
He doesn't answer. No. sorry!

600
00:58:51.261 --> 00:58:54.341
Then we just take a finger.

601
00:58:54.501 --> 00:58:59.141
- Can't you help it?
- Take it easy and breathe deeply.

602
00:58:59.301 --> 00:59:02.901
Can't you do anything else?
Hit me a little more?

603
00:59:03.061 --> 00:59:06.501
Could you be so kind?
to stop crying?

604
00:59:06.661 --> 00:59:12.301
Excuse me. Is there anything wrong?
What can I do? Anything.

605
00:59:12.461 --> 00:59:17.261
Can you put your hair up again?
So you look like a little workboy?

606
00:59:17.421 --> 00:59:20.661
Of course I can. Of course.

607
00:59:22.701 --> 00:59:27.821
- Then I have to go to the toilet.
- Yes. We are adults.

608
00:59:29.861 --> 00:59:33.621
If you try to escape.
Then I will kill you.

609
00:59:33.781 --> 00:59:35.581
I do.

610
00:59:40.301 --> 00:59:42.581
Who do you want to call?

611
00:59:51.061 --> 00:59:54.061
Phew. that was stupid of you.

612
01:00:04.821 --> 01:00:08.061
No! You're dead!

613
01:00:28.781 --> 01:00:33.741
It is completely impossible to find
a new story for a children's book.

614
01:00:33.901 --> 01:00:37.741
I have a lot of good grades.
but it's just like...

615
01:00:37.901 --> 01:00:42.261
There is something missing that makes
the universe becomes unique.

616
01:00:42.421 --> 01:00:47.501
There are over 1900 children's books
which has a duck as the main character.

617
01:00:47.661 --> 01:00:52.021
- Why aren't you sewing something?
- What should I sew?

618
01:00:52.181 --> 01:00:57.101
Sew something for those out there. They've been wearing hats.
wearing the same clothes since they arrived.

619
01:00:57.261 --> 01:01:01.101
41.7 MILLION NOK NEVER FOUND

620
01:01:12.221 --> 01:01:16.941
I like Björn. He says
I can become very good at guitar.

621
01:01:24.101 --> 01:01:26.901
Are you tired?

622
01:01:27.061 --> 01:01:31.261
If you are sorry.
You are welcome to sleep in my bed.

623
01:01:35.941 --> 01:01:40.141
Are you aware of
How much have I done for you?

624
01:01:42.221 --> 01:01:45.981
Could you be so kind?
to help me here?

625
01:02:42.101 --> 01:02:43.901
Hey.

626
01:02:45.181 --> 01:02:49.381
- That's not your axe.
- No. maybe it's theirs.

627
01:02:49.541 --> 01:02:52.861
It was here when we took over the house.
Do you want it?

628
01:02:53.021 --> 01:02:58.221
It should be inside the workshop.
it must not be taken down.

629
01:03:10.581 --> 01:03:13.461
It should hang there.

630
01:03:13.621 --> 01:03:17.501
Oh yes. I can see that.

631
01:03:18.381 --> 01:03:20.261
Like that.

632
01:03:23.101 --> 01:03:27.021
Are you the one who made it?
those signs that are all over the place?

633
01:03:27.181 --> 01:03:30.421
Those aren't signs. Those are runes.

634
01:03:30.581 --> 01:03:36.101
There are also many others
of their old Viking things here.

635
01:03:36.261 --> 01:03:38.461
Just look here.

636
01:03:40.781 --> 01:03:45.381
I'm freezing.
I don't want to be here.

637
01:03:48.301 --> 01:03:51.541
Should I make hot cocoa?

638
01:03:51.701 --> 01:03:55.821
What is Anchor?
looking for out in the woods?

639
01:03:55.981 --> 01:04:00.221
He told me that there are a lot
money. so you can say that.

640
01:04:00.381 --> 01:04:03.741
It's strange that you're driving and asking
when I don't know.

641
01:04:03.901 --> 01:04:07.621
- Why can't Anker find them?
- Because he can't remember anything.

642
01:04:07.781 --> 01:04:10.621
Not even
How to set a rune.

643
01:04:10.781 --> 01:04:13.301
Putting a rune? What does it mean?

644
01:04:13.461 --> 01:04:18.901
When you have a secret. you put
one a rune. So one can find the prey.

645
01:04:19.061 --> 01:04:24.261
And Anker wants you to
to put a rune somewhere nearby?

646
01:04:26.941 --> 01:04:31.381
I would like to see how
Do it. You can show me.

647
01:04:31.541 --> 01:04:34.581
Do you think I'm crazy?
I'm not crazy.

648
01:04:34.781 --> 01:04:37.621
It's Anker who's crazy.

649
01:04:37.781 --> 01:04:41.461
He can't remember anything.
He's the one who's crazy.

650
01:04:41.621 --> 01:04:46.101
Margrethe. do you have time to come up?
and look at something I've sewn?

651
01:04:46.261 --> 01:04:50.901
- I'm in the middle of something. Werner.
- But come on. Margrethe. Now!

652
01:04:51.061 --> 01:04:52.821
Excuse me.

653
01:06:36.781 --> 01:06:41.901
I'll probably sew it up.
I'm unsure about the colors.

654
01:06:42.061 --> 01:06:45.341
It is colored beaver.
Can we keep our clothes?

655
01:06:45.501 --> 01:06:49.221
I'll look into it.
It's probably something tax-related.

656
01:06:49.381 --> 01:06:52.421
- Good morning. Anchor.
- Good morning. John.

657
01:06:52.581 --> 01:06:55.101
Have you seen what Werner has sewn?

658
01:06:55.261 --> 01:06:59.381
And everyone has insisted on
that I should have a set too.

659
01:06:59.541 --> 01:07:03.981
I'm pushing it in the direction of the Beatles.
McCartney invented Sergeant Pepper -

660
01:07:04.141 --> 01:07:08.821
- because they were tired of being
themselves. A whole new identity.

661
01:07:08.981 --> 01:07:12.861
You probably think it's silly.
but it will work.

662
01:07:13.021 --> 01:07:17.261
I think it's absolutely brilliant.
We are on the right track.

663
01:07:17.421 --> 01:07:22.421
- Whatever you do. just keep going.
- Okay. but then I'll do it.

664
01:07:26.261 --> 01:07:28.741
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

665
01:07:32.981 --> 01:07:37.941
I know you're looking for the money.
John has told me everything.

666
01:07:40.141 --> 01:07:45.021
Relax. I'm not calling.
to the police or something.

667
01:07:45.181 --> 01:07:47.301
Why not?

668
01:07:48.581 --> 01:07:52.861
- Because I want the same thing as you.
- Ok.

669
01:07:54.821 --> 01:07:58.141
- And what is it that I want?
- I think you want to leave.

670
01:07:58.301 --> 01:08:00.861
But you can't find the money.

671
01:08:01.021 --> 01:08:04.821
I can get John to tell us.
where they are.

672
01:08:04.981 --> 01:08:07.261
Us?

673
01:08:07.421 --> 01:08:12.701
- Should we stop playing games?
- What kind of game?

674
01:08:12.861 --> 01:08:17.981
Give it to me. I've seen how
You've been looking at me since you arrived.

675
01:08:18.141 --> 01:08:22.421
And I understand that you understand
me as unattainable. but...

676
01:08:22.581 --> 01:08:27.061
...Werner and I actually don't
been happy together for many years.

677
01:08:27.221 --> 01:08:31.821
- You can't tell that from me.
- It's just a facade.

678
01:08:33.021 --> 01:08:36.941
So I'll stay with you.
when you travel.

679
01:08:47.261 --> 01:08:50.461
Have you told Margrethe?
about the money?

680
01:08:50.621 --> 01:08:55.221
No. I've only told you about runes.
You just got a lot of money.

681
01:08:55.381 --> 01:08:58.981
Now you tell me
Where is the rest of the money?

682
01:09:01.341 --> 01:09:03.661
Now comes Freya.

683
01:09:10.021 --> 01:09:11.221
Freya!

684
01:09:13.701 --> 01:09:16.941
- He hasn't followed you?
- I don't think so.

685
01:09:17.101 --> 01:09:20.501
I took the train. I didn't know
What should I do?

686
01:09:20.661 --> 01:09:24.421
- Are you okay? Is Manfred okay?
- You can't just come here.

687
01:09:24.581 --> 01:09:28.741
Do you think I would like to be here?
I hate being here!

688
01:09:28.901 --> 01:09:31.981
Then I don't understand.
why you came.

689
01:09:32.141 --> 01:09:34.901
You are really
The world's biggest asshole.

690
01:09:35.061 --> 01:09:39.861
You come. and then everything falls into place
completely crazy again.

691
01:09:40.021 --> 01:09:42.421
Can't find your money?

692
01:09:42.581 --> 01:09:47.141
Don't you think I knew what you were doing?
Should I come here? I know you.

693
01:09:47.301 --> 01:09:52.701
We have been waiting for you for so long. and
Now you are leaving and leaving everything behind.

694
01:09:54.021 --> 01:09:58.021
You promised your mother to take care of Manfred.
You swore!

695
01:09:58.181 --> 01:10:01.701
Of course I travel.
You should do that too.

696
01:10:01.861 --> 01:10:07.381
- You've wasted your life on him.
- If you travel. you are like a father.

697
01:10:07.541 --> 01:10:11.821
Shut up! Don't touch me like that!

698
01:10:14.381 --> 01:10:19.821
Sometimes I think I see Dad
in places where there are many people.

699
01:10:19.981 --> 01:10:23.221
Then I dream about
that he says sorry.

700
01:10:23.381 --> 01:10:29.261
I just don't understand how to
can leave a family like that.

701
01:10:29.421 --> 01:10:33.341
I know that
It's insane. but...

702
01:10:33.501 --> 01:10:39.261
I still believe he will come and
give a speech if I'm getting married.

703
01:10:39.421 --> 01:10:42.741
You and Mom have been talking about him for 40 years.

704
01:10:42.901 --> 01:10:45.821
Go ahead.
The man found another family.

705
01:10:45.981 --> 01:10:51.181
Because he couldn't handle Manfred.
And no one does that.

706
01:10:56.941 --> 01:11:02.541
Dad was a piece of shit. Freja. You should
Just be glad he left.

707
01:11:02.701 --> 01:11:07.901
Father was also other things. It is
no people who are just one thing.

708
01:11:13.981 --> 01:11:18.381
- Shouldn't John help?
- Come on. Paul George.

709
01:11:18.541 --> 01:11:23.621
Stop calling me.
Paul George! John. are you in?

710
01:11:25.341 --> 01:11:28.861
Come and help.
Stop feeling sorry for yourself now.

711
01:11:29.021 --> 01:11:32.301
Hey. hey. hey!
Pay attention to the epaulette.

712
01:11:32.461 --> 01:11:38.581
- You're not even in the band.
- No one understands what you're saying.

713
01:11:38.741 --> 01:11:43.301
- Swedish idiot.
- Am I a Swedish idiot?

714
01:11:43.461 --> 01:11:47.221
- What are you doing?
- At least I'm not an alcoholic.

715
01:11:47.381 --> 01:11:52.021
Then the clothes are gone. Now!
The gift shop is now closing.

716
01:11:52.181 --> 01:11:55.821
- Take off your clothes!
- Save the power of the instruments.

717
01:11:55.981 --> 01:11:58.901
Do you really think
that you can fool someone?

718
01:11:59.061 --> 01:12:03.701
You know very well that
you don't have blue eyes or blond hair.

719
01:12:03.861 --> 01:12:08.461
You are not Bjorn.
and you never will be. Fucking clown!

720
01:12:09.781 --> 01:12:11.901
No! Not the guitar!

721
01:12:12.821 --> 01:12:15.341
- Paul!
- I'm out!

722
01:12:15.501 --> 01:12:17.781
- George?
- Werner?

723
01:12:17.941 --> 01:12:21.781
- Bear?
- I'm out. It's over!

724
01:12:21.941 --> 01:12:26.741
Okay. he's going for a little walk.
and then we drive.

725
01:12:28.701 --> 01:12:34.021
Not here either. I'm going crazy.
I can't take it anymore.

726
01:12:35.861 --> 01:12:39.141
You have to make him understand.
that we are dying from this here.

727
01:12:39.301 --> 01:12:43.901
Can't we just leave without that money?
It doesn't matter now.

728
01:12:44.061 --> 01:12:47.981
- Because you're going to jail for this.
- For what then?

729
01:12:48.141 --> 01:12:52.221
For letting those lunatics go
out of the hospital.

730
01:12:52.381 --> 01:12:56.901
- Why do you say that?
- They know it's you.

731
01:12:57.061 --> 01:13:01.941
I have no idea what the penalty is.
to kidnap four patients.

732
01:13:02.101 --> 01:13:06.061
But it was Lothar.
I was just helping get Manfred out.

733
01:13:06.221 --> 01:13:10.661
- And there were three patients.
- There are four in the newspapers.

734
01:13:15.301 --> 01:13:17.941
4 PATIENTS MISSING
IN DENMARK AND SWEDEN

735
01:13:35.701 --> 01:13:40.261
Paul George has beaten Werner and
left the band. so the two of us have to join.

736
01:13:40.421 --> 01:13:44.781
- I need you. Now.
- Over 25 people have purchased tickets.

737
01:13:44.941 --> 01:13:49.661
We have massive problems in the band.
and a huge concert in three hours.

738
01:13:49.821 --> 01:13:54.421
If I had known it was like this
Manager... Don't worry. I have a plan!

739
01:13:54.581 --> 01:13:58.781
Shut up now!
Now it ends... Kjeld.

740
01:13:58.941 --> 01:14:04.101
- Why do you call him Kjeld?
- Because his name is Kjeld.

741
01:14:04.261 --> 01:14:07.261
- He is a psychiatric patient.
- Isn't everyone?

742
01:14:07.421 --> 01:14:10.421
Exactly. Margaret.
I've been saying that all along.

743
01:14:10.581 --> 01:14:13.381
Lothar Kjeld Gerner Nielsen.
psychiatric patient.

744
01:14:13.541 --> 01:14:16.501
Why are you angry?
that my name is Kjeld?

745
01:14:16.661 --> 01:14:20.421
- And you're not dying. are you?
- Shut up and sit still.

746
01:14:20.581 --> 01:14:25.741
- I might be dying.
- Now you hold the fuck up!

747
01:14:25.901 --> 01:14:28.861
I've been sewing for 14 hours straight!

748
01:14:29.021 --> 01:14:32.501
I'm running on seven hours of sleep.
And you know what?

749
01:14:32.661 --> 01:14:37.381
Right now I just have to have
and a glass of Burgundy. Okay?

750
01:14:39.781 --> 01:14:42.101
No! Anchor!

751
01:14:43.981 --> 01:14:45.621
Anchor...

752
01:14:52.661 --> 01:14:55.381
- Anchor!
- Did you see that?

753
01:14:55.541 --> 01:14:59.941
He hit him.
He hit him with a frying pan.

754
01:15:02.061 --> 01:15:05.901
Now he dies.
Now he dies too. Everyone dies.

755
01:15:06.061 --> 01:15:09.621
- No one is dying.
- Yes. he dies.

756
01:15:11.061 --> 01:15:13.901
- And then I get sent away.
- Give it to me.

757
01:15:14.061 --> 01:15:17.381
Why don't you go out?
and are you practicing for the concert now?

758
01:15:17.541 --> 01:15:22.781
I swear. you touch that guitar
again. I'll crush your head.

759
01:15:24.821 --> 01:15:29.101
And yes. you're right. We all die.
together. and it's your fault.

760
01:15:29.261 --> 01:15:32.581
No. Anker. don't worry.
That's not true.

761
01:15:33.861 --> 01:15:37.661
Look at me.
Look at Freya.

762
01:15:37.821 --> 01:15:41.861
- Look at her. It's your fault.
- Hold up now.

763
01:15:42.021 --> 01:15:46.181
It's your fault we're in this mess.
It's your fault that Dad left.

764
01:15:46.341 --> 01:15:50.261
- It's all your fault.
- Stop it now. damn it!

765
01:15:50.421 --> 01:15:52.421
No. John. Wait. John!

766
01:15:52.581 --> 01:15:54.581
No. don't!

767
01:16:54.821 --> 01:16:56.821
- Jump in.
- In the.

768
01:16:56.981 --> 01:16:59.821
- Have you been crying?
- Go. I'll take the bus.

769
01:16:59.981 --> 01:17:05.061
- It's not embarrassing. I've cried.
- I've cried a lot more.

770
01:17:06.701 --> 01:17:11.901
- We can try to say sorry.
- No. I'm going to Germany.

771
01:17:12.061 --> 01:17:16.861
- But what if we could get the band together?
- I'm going to Germany!

772
01:17:17.021 --> 01:17:20.621
Holocaust! I'll stop it.
and you shall not hinder me.

773
01:17:20.781 --> 01:17:25.381
I could never have dreamed of that.
But maybe I can drive with you?

774
01:17:31.021 --> 01:17:33.661
Lothar. answer me honestly.

775
01:17:35.821 --> 01:17:40.581
I don't have blond hair.
and aren't my eyes blue?

776
01:17:40.781 --> 01:17:45.621
I'm going crazy. I don't know.
if what I see is true.

777
01:17:46.981 --> 01:17:49.981
Damn... I see...

778
01:17:50.141 --> 01:17:54.101
- I don't see blue eyes and blond hair.
- Oh no!

779
01:17:54.261 --> 01:17:58.141
I see a dark person
with an impressive beard growth.

780
01:17:58.301 --> 01:18:01.941
But it doesn't matter.
what I see. Or others.

781
01:18:02.101 --> 01:18:04.741
What counts is what you see.

782
01:18:04.901 --> 01:18:08.341
I see the most talented
the member of the band.

783
01:18:08.501 --> 01:18:13.581
And then I see an incredibly handsome man.
who is in deep balance with himself.

784
01:18:13.741 --> 01:18:17.861
And I see a very good colleague
who could go solo.

785
01:18:22.141 --> 01:18:24.101
Yes.

786
01:18:24.261 --> 01:18:27.341
- That's good. Jump in.
- Ok.

787
01:19:16.661 --> 01:19:19.301
Can I help you with something?

788
01:19:29.701 --> 01:19:31.501
At.

789
01:19:51.301 --> 01:19:53.181
Anchor!

790
01:20:16.301 --> 01:20:18.221
Anchor?

791
01:20:19.861 --> 01:20:22.981
Flemming. take it easy.

792
01:20:26.421 --> 01:20:28.301
Anchor?

793
01:20:29.261 --> 01:20:32.221
I need the money. Anker.

794
01:20:35.901 --> 01:20:39.021
They're not yours. I don't have them.

795
01:20:39.181 --> 01:20:43.661
Or. I've tried calling.
I'll have them soon.

796
01:20:43.821 --> 01:20:49.301
I'll cut off a finger from your brother.
then you have ten seconds to think.

797
01:20:49.461 --> 01:20:53.941
- And then I cut another one and another one.
- Flemming. don't do it.

798
01:20:54.101 --> 01:20:57.781
You will get money.
I just have to find them.

799
01:20:57.941 --> 01:21:02.781
I would like to give you some money.
but I don't know where they are!

800
01:21:08.341 --> 01:21:12.501
Okay. I just got it.
never experienced before.

801
01:21:12.661 --> 01:21:17.821
- Normally people scream so exaggeratedly.
- Don't do anything to him anymore.

802
01:21:17.981 --> 01:21:21.301
- Only he knows where they are.
- Don't say anything. I can handle it.

803
01:21:21.461 --> 01:21:26.221
- Do you know where the money is. Manfred?
- John. His name is John.

804
01:21:26.381 --> 01:21:30.261
- Do you know where the money is. John?
- They're down by the sea.

805
01:21:30.421 --> 01:21:33.981
But I don't show it.
if you do anything to my brother.

806
01:21:34.141 --> 01:21:38.061
Now you did something to my brother.
so now I won't show it.

807
01:21:38.221 --> 01:21:40.581
Now I'll never find the money.

808
01:21:40.741 --> 01:21:44.341
- Why am I going out here?
- Get in the car. You drive.

809
01:21:45.661 --> 01:21:48.901
- Drive.
- I'm not allowed to drive a car.

810
01:21:49.061 --> 01:21:54.101
I can only drive with automatic transmission.
And I just lost a finger.

811
01:21:54.261 --> 01:21:59.301
- I don't want to be without Anker.
- Then I'll shoot you in the throat.

812
01:21:59.461 --> 01:22:03.421
- I know. Where do you want to be taken?
- For the money.

813
01:22:03.621 --> 01:22:07.781
We can't. The money is Anker's.
I can't tell anyone.

814
01:22:07.941 --> 01:22:12.421
Now that hand hurts a little.
I'm hungry too.

815
01:22:12.581 --> 01:22:16.221
Can we have some food?
And I'm a little cold.

816
01:22:16.381 --> 01:22:20.981
Yes. Then we'll drive.
Then drive... Now I'm driving.

817
01:22:21.141 --> 01:22:25.941
How do you get it to run?
It's really difficult.

818
01:22:26.101 --> 01:22:29.221
I can't!
I have to... Now I'm driving.

819
01:22:42.781 --> 01:22:46.741
It is very illegal.
what you have done here.

820
01:22:50.181 --> 01:22:53.861
- A small animal crosses the road.
- Shut up now.

821
01:22:54.021 --> 01:22:57.781
- And breathe normally.
- But I can't do that.

822
01:23:01.861 --> 01:23:06.461
- You don't need to drive faster.
- Anker is looking after me. Let's leave it alone.

823
01:23:06.621 --> 01:23:11.861
- You mustn't do anything to him.
- Don't drive so fast.

824
01:23:14.461 --> 01:23:18.581
- Slow down. you idiot.
- Promise you won't kill Anker.

825
01:23:20.461 --> 01:23:25.101
Slow down.
Slow down. Manfred!

826
01:24:16.181 --> 01:24:21.501
You have very big mental problems.
problems in your family. Do you know that?

827
01:24:21.661 --> 01:24:23.061
Yes.

828
01:24:58.061 --> 01:24:59.861
Anchor!

829
01:25:24.861 --> 01:25:26.781
Anchor.

830
01:25:29.661 --> 01:25:31.621
Anchor.

831
01:25:58.861 --> 01:26:01.021
Manfred!

832
01:26:16.781 --> 01:26:18.701
John!

833
01:26:39.381 --> 01:26:41.301
Manfred!

834
01:26:46.421 --> 01:26:48.341
Manfred!

835
01:28:12.901 --> 01:28:15.781
My girl. Daddy loves you.

836
01:28:15.941 --> 01:28:20.341
See you on Sunday. And the food is
ready-made. you just have to heat it.

837
01:29:07.781 --> 01:29:10.341
Nei. nei. nei. nei!

838
01:29:15.021 --> 01:29:19.941
- Something terrible has happened.
- Something about mother and Freja?

839
01:29:20.101 --> 01:29:22.861
They killed him. He's dead.

840
01:29:23.021 --> 01:29:26.701
- Who?
- Join us.

841
01:30:10.341 --> 01:30:12.981
Call for an ambulance.

842
01:30:17.341 --> 01:30:22.101
Just wait until I get up.
Manfred. Then I'll crush you.

843
01:30:22.261 --> 01:30:27.981
You won't be able to walk. You
You won't be able to move.

844
01:30:28.141 --> 01:30:30.861
Help me! Help dad!

845
01:30:55.901 --> 01:30:58.341
Look away. Manfred.

846
01:30:58.501 --> 01:31:02.301
Anchor. what are you doing? Anchor?

847
01:31:06.981 --> 01:31:13.141
John Lennon was hit by four
shots when he arrived at his home.

848
01:31:13.301 --> 01:31:17.221
He was rushed to the hospital.
where he was declared dead.

849
01:31:17.381 --> 01:31:22.581
The perpetrator. Mark David
Chapman. is a fanatical fan...

850
01:31:53.541 --> 01:31:56.421
We never talk about this.

851
01:31:56.581 --> 01:32:00.741
You must swear on
that you don't say anything to anyone.

852
01:32:00.901 --> 01:32:04.261
You stop being a Viking. okay?

853
01:32:07.221 --> 01:32:10.181
You can never be that again.

854
01:33:08.101 --> 01:33:12.941
I was out picking mushrooms with my mother.
but I didn't say anything.

855
01:33:15.301 --> 01:33:18.061
Mother stood right above him.

856
01:33:24.221 --> 01:33:27.541
Are you sorry?
that I showed you?

857
01:33:34.581 --> 01:33:38.541
I think I knew it in a way.

858
01:33:43.741 --> 01:33:47.541
I thought it was something
I had dreamed.

859
01:33:51.821 --> 01:33:54.501
Freja often does that too.

860
01:33:59.621 --> 01:34:02.741
- Doesn't Freya know?
- In the.

861
01:34:02.901 --> 01:34:05.541
But she dreams of him.

862
01:34:06.661 --> 01:34:11.221
She is so sad about it.
I think she wants to know.

863
01:34:15.741 --> 01:34:18.981
You're welcome to tell her.

864
01:34:27.541 --> 01:34:30.741
Should I tell her?
for both of us?

865
01:34:30.901 --> 01:34:35.461
Do you dare? I will.
I would really appreciate it if you did.

866
01:34:44.421 --> 01:34:47.101
I know you are going your way.

867
01:34:48.381 --> 01:34:50.661
You're embarrassed by me.

868
01:34:50.821 --> 01:34:55.061
I'm not always so good.
to be together with.

869
01:34:58.861 --> 01:35:02.541
There is no one
which is okay all the time.

870
01:35:03.501 --> 01:35:06.381
You have to be exactly what you want.

871
01:35:32.221 --> 01:35:36.381
- What happened?
- Yes. I found her this morning.

872
01:35:36.541 --> 01:35:39.981
She fell by accident.
on one of the stones.

873
01:35:40.141 --> 01:35:43.741
We are home now.
Come on. come on. Come on. come on.

874
01:35:43.901 --> 01:35:48.181
- Can I do something?
- No. She needs to take it easy.

875
01:35:52.221 --> 01:35:57.101
I think I'll make some soup.
She has lost a lot of teeth.

876
01:38:16.781 --> 01:38:21.741
Okay. so let's just take it.
Have I lied about who I am?

877
01:38:24.581 --> 01:38:31.141
Yes. maybe. My father was a trustee.
at IKEA in Ballerup. not Taastrup.

878
01:38:31.301 --> 01:38:37.341
The Taastrup branch only opened after
that they closed the Ballerup branch.

879
01:38:38.301 --> 01:38:41.381
So yes. my father was the boss -

880
01:38:41.541 --> 01:38:45.781
- in the only IKEA store
that was ever closed.

881
01:38:45.941 --> 01:38:50.341
You are aware of what such things are.
do with a small family.

882
01:38:50.501 --> 01:38:54.061
Does that make me a bad person?
that I am a dreamer -

883
01:38:54.221 --> 01:38:57.781
- that I don't always hang myself
in fantasy and reality -

884
01:38:57.941 --> 01:39:01.581
- and that I'm just trying
to recreate the world's best band -

885
01:39:01.741 --> 01:39:05.261
- Well. then you're welcome.
Call me sick.

886
01:39:06.781 --> 01:39:13.021
And if you want to hit me again. then...
Björn and I bought a new frying pan.

887
01:39:18.421 --> 01:39:22.181
Can you forgive me. Anker? What?

888
01:39:24.061 --> 01:39:26.221
Are you angry with me?

889
01:39:31.501 --> 01:39:35.341
I forgive. I'm not angry.

890
01:39:37.181 --> 01:39:39.781
Thank you. Anchor.

891
01:41:03.301 --> 01:41:06.741
- Okay. Now it's them.
- This one is not good. Smell.

892
01:41:06.901 --> 01:41:09.621
- I can't smell anything.
- Shut up now.

893
01:41:09.781 --> 01:41:13.261
What an afternoon. huh?
For et show!

894
01:41:13.421 --> 01:41:16.421
Does he have to bring the axe on stage?
It is dangerous.

895
01:41:16.581 --> 01:41:21.221
It's way too big. How did you
allowed to bring it in?

896
01:41:21.381 --> 01:41:25.741
- You can bring axes again.
- Not on stage!

897
01:41:25.901 --> 01:41:27.901
The Flying Beavers!

898
01:41:28.061 --> 01:41:30.981
Then you can't play with us.

899
01:41:33.301 --> 01:41:39.061
If you would like to have it with you. then
bring it. But you don't need it.

900
01:44:45.821 --> 01:44:49.301
There are many different
people in this world.

901
01:44:49.461 --> 01:44:54.941
And under the great chieftain was
everyone was happy. and everyone was equal.

902
01:44:55.101 --> 01:44:57.861
Everyone was equally happy.

903
01:44:58.021 --> 01:45:02.941
Of course there were bumps in the road.
and battles that had to be fought.

904
01:45:03.101 --> 01:45:07.701
But the great chief was always thinking about
that everyone is worth the same.

905
01:45:07.861 --> 01:45:13.301
And he knew that when everyone is missing
a foot. no one is missing a foot.

906
01:45:17.421 --> 01:45:22.541
As the years went by. everyone just became
even happier than they already were.

907
01:45:22.701 --> 01:45:26.581
Even though a people who lack
limbs have poor balance -

908
01:45:26.781 --> 01:45:31.261
- and shouldn't throw axes after
each other. they didn't hold back.

909
01:45:31.421 --> 01:45:36.581
Because if everyone has poor balance.
so no one has bad balance.

910
01:45:40.581 --> 01:45:44.381
As the day wore on
where the unthinkable happened -

911
01:45:44.541 --> 01:45:49.701
- the great chief didn't think for long
before he made his decision.

912
01:45:55.181 --> 01:45:58.101
Many were afraid.
but no one wanted to say it out loud.

913
01:45:58.261 --> 01:46:03.461
And the great chieftain laid. as
the last one. his head on the block.

914
01:46:03.621 --> 01:46:07.021
And in the seconds before
the axe hit his neck -

915
01:46:07.181 --> 01:46:12.821
- he looked out over his people. and a
Blessed peace spread in his heart.

916
01:46:12.981 --> 01:46:16.661
For all the maladjusted and
outcasts. those who were different -

917
01:46:16.821 --> 01:46:20.901
- the weak. the sick. the rich. the poor.
the pretty and the ugly -

918
01:46:21.061 --> 01:46:25.301
- the men and the women. and all those
who didn't know who they were...

919
01:46:25.461 --> 01:46:29.341
...he had never seen them
more calm and balanced -

920
01:46:29.501 --> 01:46:33.181
- and finally everyone was
worth just as much.

921
01:46:42.741 --> 01:46:49.101
Werner de König
THE LAST VIKING

922
01:50:51.061 --> 01:50:54.061
Norwegian lyrics: Nina Maria Eidheim
Scandinavian Text Service

